<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="B1930"><font color="red">Early 1930</font> <i>Our Friend James Joyce</i> by Mary and Padraic Colum (Gloucester, Mass: Peter Smith, 1958) page 103: As I look over the text of <cite>Haveth Childers Everywhere</cite>, I come to &ldquo;tendulcis tunes like water parted &hellip;&rdquo; &ldquo;Water parted,&rdquo; I cried as I typed this passage. &ldquo;You&apos;re drawing on Goldsmith, Joyce.&rdquo; </div>
